WhatNew Wholesale Category Policy

WhatNew Support July 1, 2025 at 2:50 AM

{/* ===== Seller Wholesale Category Section ===== */}

WhatNew Wholesale Category Policy

WhatNew’s Wholesale Category is designed to support high volume transactions and reseller product sourcing, which includes the sale of entire pallets, casepacks, and bundled inventory. Given the nature of these transactions, WhatNew has implemented specific policies to promote transparency, consistency, and trust between sellers and buyers.

WhatNew’s Wholesale Category is currently limited to sellers in the U.S., France, and Germany. The Wholesale Category in France and Germany is currently in beta testing; for more on selling Wholesale in these regions, see below.

On this page:

  • What is sold in the Wholesale category (US)
  • Buyers in Wholesale Category (US)
  • Seller Requirements – Wholesale Category (US)

What is sold in the Wholesale category (US)

In the Wholesale Category, there are two subcategories:

  • Pallets
  • Casepacks & Bundles

Selling in the Pallets Subcategory

A pallet is a bulk collection of items in wholesale quantities (typically 100+ items). Pallet inventory can be wholesale (direct from manufacturer/distributor) or liquidation inventory (e.g., overstock, returned, or past-season stock). Pallets will ship via Freight through our external partner Blue Grace.

Selling in Casepacks & Bundles Subcategory

Casepacks & bundles are lots of 10+ units intended for resale. Typically, casepacks are made up of multiples of the same item, while bundles are mixed inventory. These lots are organized in a box and shipped via standard WhatNew shipping labels.

Buyers in Wholesale Category (US)

Buyers should carefully review the seller’s manifest (as applicable), listing details, and ask relevant questions to understand what they’re buying (e.g., direct from manufacturer vs liquidation) and the condition of items.

Buyer Shipping Considerations

  • Pallets: Sellers must ship within 3 business days. Freight carriers will contact buyers within 3 business days. Average delivery is 1–3 weeks.
  • Casepacks & Bundles: Must be shipped within 2 business days, following WhatNew’s general shipping policy.
  • Buyer phone number: Shared with seller for coordinating pallet delivery with freight carrier.

Seller Requirements – Wholesale Category (US)

Sellers must be in possession of the pallet, casepack, or bundle and show it during their show. All sales within the Wholesale Category must comply with WhatNew’s Surprise Product Policy.

Pallet Disclosure Requirements

  • Type of items (e.g., shoes)
  • Quantity of items
  • Condition of items
  • [Optional] Brand(s) included
  • [Optional] MSRP of entire lot
  • [Optional] Estimated number of unique SKUs

Casepack & Bundle Disclosure

Detailed manifests are not required. However, sellers must comply with the Single Surprise Product Policy — listings must accurately describe item contents so buyers know what to expect.

Condition Details

  • Accurately describe the condition of all items.
  • Disclose any defects, damage, missing parts, or wear and tear.

No Individual Items in Pallet Category

Sellers cannot list individual items pulled from pallets in this category. For mixed lots or single items, use the Casepacks & Bundles subcategory or another WhatNew category.

Prohibited or Restricted Items

Sellers in the Wholesale Category must comply with WhatNew’s Prohibited or Restricted Items Policy and Counterfeit Policy. The following are not permitted:

  • Expired items (less than 3 months from expiration)
  • Cosmetics older than 3 years
  • Items marked “Not for resale”

Shipping in Wholesale

Shipping Pallets

  • Ship within 3 business days via Blue Grace Logistics.
  • Update tracking through BYOL (Bring Your Own Label).
  • Sales limited to contiguous U.S. only.

Shipping Casepacks & Bundles

  • Ship within 2 business days, per WhatNew’s shipping policy.

Refunds

Sellers must comply with WhatNew’s Buyer Protection Policy for refunds.

Tax Exemption

  • Apply before purchasing: Submit a sales tax exemption certificate, government-issued ID, and business permit/resale certificate.
  • No retroactive refunds: Sales tax cannot be refunded for past orders if exemption was not applied before purchase.

Helpful Walkthroughs & Resources

  • Scheduling a pallet show and creating a listing
  • Running your pallet show
  • Fulfillment and uploading tracking information
